


	Everything is available in the from of Rest API's which are present in Selenium client library


	W3C WebDriver protocol is used in Selenium 4 in place of json wire protocol


	Advantages of W3C WebDriver:
	1.protocol Standards ---> common code
	2.Stability
	3.Actions API --->> Two keys press , zoom in or out , drag and drop.
	4.Code is backward compatibility.
	5.Wont impact the code 
	6.added extra or removed desired capabilities


	Selenium 3.8 to 3.14.59 version uses json wire protocol + W3C WebDriver
	Selenium 4 W3C WebDriver


	In Selenium 4

	IDE +    uses W3C WebDriver protocol
